The NPA’s Investigating Directorate and the Hawks are confident the net is closing in on those accused of squandering money from state-owned parastatal, Transnet. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former Transnet Group CEO Siyabona Gama, who was arrested for corruption, has denied all charges against him. Gama was among five suspects who handed themselves over at the Brackendowns Police station on Friday morning. WATCH | Former Transnet GCEO Gama, co-accused granted bail The five are accused of contravening the Public Finance Management Act, fraud, corruption and money laundering. The matter against the accused has been postponed to 13 June. WATCH: Former Transnet executives appear in court The NPA says more arrests are expected. * eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones reports.